<HEAD>DUKE OF YORK's ARMY.</HEAD>
<OPENER><DATELINE><HI>Head Quarters, Tourney,</HI> <DATE><HI>Dec.</HI> 13, 1793.</DATE></DATELINE></OPENER>
<P>HIS Royal Highne&s;s orders, that all the troops under his command pay proper re&s;pect to the <HI>Ho&s;t,</HI> and all other religious proce&s;&s;ions. He directs, that <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ll centinels carry their arms when any religious proce&s;&s;ion is pa&s;&s;ing; and demands the attention of all officer<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">, but particularly of tho&s;e on duty, to prevent the &s;<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="4 letters">e&s;t impropriety being committed on the&s;e occa&s;ions.</P>
<P>His Royal Highne&s;s is confident, that the troops under his command will ever bear in mind, that though we differ in &s;ome of the ceremonies of reli|gion, we unite with our gallant allies; and it is our glory to do &s;o, in every &s;entiment of devotion to our CREATOR, and attachment and loyalty to our SO|VEREIGNS.</P>
