<OPENER><DATELINE><DATE><HI>Monday, December</HI> 16, 1793.</DATE></DATELINE></OPENER>
<P>A Deputation from the Commune of DIJON in|formed the Convention, that <HI>various</HI> SAINTS of BOTH <HI>Sexes,</HI> GOLD and SILVER, would arrive in a &s;ew days. We gave them nothing to cat on the road, &s;aid the Orator, becau&s;e we are told they can change &s;tone to bread, and water to wine. We a&s;ked what kind of carriage they would chu&s;e? To which they replied, That, being Saints of Burgundy, they &s;hould prefer wine ca&s;ks; and in two or three days you will &s;o receive them, with flaggons once thought &s;acred. (Honourable mention, and in&s;ertion in the Bulletin.)</P>
